What This Credit Actually Is

Not a currency in the normal sense.

It represents:

Verified contribution of your data to real outcomes

Each credit encodes:
	•	who generated it (user)
	•	what type of signal it came from
	•	where it was used (domain)
	•	how much impact it had
	•	under what constraints (consent)

So instead of:

“you have $10”

